data.enText: to put an end, often by force, to a group or an activity that is believed to threaten authority

data.chText: 起义遭到了残酷的镇压。

data.enText: to prevent sth from being published or made known

data.chText: 警方被指隐瞒关键证据。
data.enText: The police were accused of suppressing vital evidence.
to prevent yourself from having or expressing a feeling or an emotion
She was unable to suppress her anger.
to prevent sth from growing, developing or continuing

simple_means.memory_skill: sup 下 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 压下去 → 镇压；忍住

tr: reduce the incidence or severity of or stop
example: this drug can suppress the hemorrhage

tr: to put down by force or authority
of emotions, desires, impulses, or behavior
come down on or keep down by unjust use of one's authority

value.def: If someone in authority suppresses an activity, they prevent it from continuing, by using force or making it illegal.

example.ex: ...drug traffickers, who continue to flourish despite international attempts to suppress them...
example.tran: 在国际社会强力打击下活动依然猖獗的贩毒分子

example.ex: ...nationwide demonstrations for democracy, suppressed after 7 weeks by the army.
example.tran: 在进行7周后遭到军队镇压的全国性民主示威活动

example.ex: ...people who were imprisoned after the violent suppression of the pro-democracy movement protests.
example.tran: 在拥护民主的抗议活动遭到暴力镇压后被投入监狱的人们

value.def: If a natural function or reaction of your body is suppressed, it is stopped, for example by drugs or illness.

example.ex: The reproduction and growth of the cancerous cells can be suppressed by bombarding them with radiation.
example.tran: 可以通过放疗杀死癌细胞来抑制其再生和扩散。

example.ex: ...the strongest evidence so far that ultraviolet light can suppress human immune responses.
example.tran: 迄今为止可证明紫外线能抑制人体免疫反应的最有力证据

value.tran: 制止，阻止，抑制(身体的功能或反应)

example.ex: Eye problems can indicate an unhealthy lifestyle with subsequent suppression of the immune system.
example.tran: 患眼疾可能表明生活方式不健康，而且免疫系统同时受到抑制。

value.def: If you suppress your feelings or reactions, you do not express them, even though you might want to.

example.ex: Liz thought of Barry and suppressed a smile...
example.tran: 莉兹想起了巴里，忍住没笑。

example.ex: The Professor said that deep sleep allowed suppressed anxieties to surface.
example.tran: 教授说深度睡眠可以使压抑的焦虑情绪得以释放。

value.tran: 抑制，控制，克制(感情或反应);忍住

example.ex: A mother's suppression of her own feelings can cause problems.
example.tran: 母亲压抑自己的情感会产生问题。

value.def: If someone suppresses a piece of information, they prevent other people from learning it.

example.ex: At no time did they try to persuade me to suppress the information...
example.tran: 他们从没有试图劝我隐瞒这个消息。

example.ex: The wrong criminal is in the dock either because a genuine mistake has been made or because evidence has been suppressed.
example.tran: 冤案错案的出现，要么是因为确实弄错了，要么是因为证据被隐瞒。

example.ex: The inspectors found no evidence which supported any allegation of suppression of official documents.
example.tran: 检察官没有找到任何证据来证实有关官方文件被封锁的说法。

value.def: If someone or something suppresses a process or activity, they stop it continuing or developing.

example.ex: 'The Government is suppressing inflation by devastating the economy,' he said...
example.tran: 他说，“政府正在通过破坏经济来抑制通货膨胀。”

example.ex: Lawyers said today's ruling would lead to higher prices and would suppress innovation of new products.
example.tran: 律师们称今天的裁决将会抬升价格，并抑制新产品的创新。

value.tran: 压制，抑制，阻止(进程或活动)

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to press, to force 挤压；逼迫
rootsaffixes.title: press

partsOfSpeech.dec: com 加强 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 压缩
com 加强 + press 挤压；逼迫 + ible 可…的 → 可压缩的
com 加强 + press 挤压；逼迫 + ion 表动作 → 压缩
de 向下 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 向下压 → 使情绪低下
depress 压下；使沮丧 + ion 表名词 → 沮丧；萧条
ex 出 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 把〔思想〕挤出来 → 表达
express 表达 + ion 表名词 → 表达；表情
im 进入 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 压进去 → 留印象
impress 盖印；留印象 + ion 表名词 → 印象；感想
impress 盖印；留印象 + ive …的 → 给人深刻印象的
op 加强 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 拼命压 → 压迫，虐待
oppress 压迫，虐待 + ion 表名词 → 压迫；苦难
press 挤压；逼迫 + ing 正…的 → 急迫的
press 挤压；逼迫 + ure 表结果 → 压力
re 回 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 压回去 → 镇压；抑制〔感情〕
sup 下 + press 挤压；逼迫 → 压下去 → 镇压；忍住
suppress 镇压；忍住（眼泪等）+ ion 表名词 → 镇压

rootsaffixes.indicate: 等在同辅音词根前, 下
rootsaffixes.title: suc-, suf-, sup-

partsOfSpeech.dec: suc 下 + ceed 走 → 从下面走到上面 → 成功
suc 下 + cumb 躺 → 躺到地下 → 死亡
suf 下 + fer 带 → 带到下面 → 受苦
suf 下 + fix 固定 → 固定在〔单词〕下面〔末尾〕→ 后缀
suf 下 + fus 流 + e → 在下面流 → 弥漫
sup 下 + plant 种植 → 种在下面 → 取代
sup 下 + plic 重叠 + ant …的 →〔双膝〕一起向下 → 哀求的
sup 下 + port 送 → 从下面送来的〔力量〕→ 支持
sup 下 + pos 放 + e → 放在〔心〕下 → 推测
sup 下 + press 压 → 镇压
